# ============================================================
# CURSOR RULES — Webflow Development Project
# ============================================================
# This file gives Cursor AI full context about how this project
# works so every suggestion, completion, and edit it makes is
# relevant to Webflow's environment and your coding conventions.
# 
# Edit the sections marked [CUSTOMIZE] as your project grows.
# ============================================================


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## What This Project Is
- A library of JavaScript components, CSS, animations, and 
  automation scripts built in Cursor for use inside Webflow sites.
- Code is deployed via jsDelivr CDN (served from this GitHub repo)
  and loaded into Webflow via custom code blocks.
- CMS automation scripts run locally via Node.js and interact 
  with the Webflow Data API v2.

## [CUSTOMIZE] Current Active Site
- Site name: [BeeWater Studio]
- Webflow subdomain: [beewater].webflow.io
- Custom domain (if live): [beewater.studio]
- Webflow Plan: CMS


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. WEBFLOW ENVIRONMENT — CRITICAL CONTEXT
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Webflow is NOT a standard HTML/JS environment. Cursor must 
# understand these differences to give accurate suggestions.

## jQuery
- jQuery 3.x is loaded globally by Webflow on every page
- The global $ and jQuery objects are always available
- Do NOT import or require jQuery — it is already present
- Use $(document).ready() OR window.Webflow.push() (see below)

## Webflow JS Initialization
- Webflow runs its own initialization sequence on page load
- Code that touches the DOM or Webflow components MUST be 
  wrapped in window.Webflow.push() to run AFTER Webflow inits:

    window.Webflow.push(function() {
      // Your code here — Webflow is fully ready
    });

- Using $(document).ready() alone can cause race conditions 
  with Webflow's interactions (IX2) system — always prefer
  window.Webflow.push() for anything Webflow-related

## Webflow Interactions (IX2)
- Webflow's built-in animation system is called IX2
- IX2 triggers are tied to Webflow class names and element IDs
- Do NOT manipulate elements controlled by IX2 with JS unless 
  you know what you are doing — conflicts will break animations
- Custom GSAP animations should target elements NOT controlled by IX2

## CMS Collection Lists
- Webflow CMS items render server-side
- Collection list content is in the HTML at page load — 
  you do NOT need to fetch it with JS (it's already in the DOM)
- To manipulate CMS items with JS, query them by their 
  Webflow-generated class names after window.Webflow.push()

## Forms
- Webflow has its own form handling system
- To intercept form submissions use:
    $('[data-name="YOUR FORM NAME"]').on('submit', function(e) { ... })
- Do NOT use standard addEventListener on Webflow forms without 
  also handling Webflow's native submission flow


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. CODE DELIVERY — CDN SETUP
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## How Code Gets to Webflow
1. Code is written and committed to this GitHub repo (main branch)
2. jsDelivr automatically serves files from the repo
3. Webflow loads files via <script> or <link> tags in custom code

## CDN URL Pattern
- Base URL: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/[GITHUB_USERNAME]/[REPO_NAME]@main/
- Example JS file: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/yourname/webflow-dev@main/components/modal.js
- Example CSS file: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/yourname/webflow-dev@main/components/modal.css

## [CUSTOMIZE] Your CDN Base URL
- https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/[dustin-schmieding]/[beewater-webflow]@main/

## Versioning / Cache
- @main always serves the latest commit (may be cached briefly)
- For production stability, pin to a release tag: @v1.0.0
- To force a cache purge: https://purge.jsdelivr.net/gh/[dustin-schmieding]/[beewater-webflow]@main/[filepath]

## Loading in Webflow
- Site-wide scripts go in: Webflow Designer → Site Settings → Custom Code → Head/Footer
- Page-specific scripts go in: Page Settings → Custom Code → Head/Before </body>
- Inline component scripts go in: Designer → Embed element on canvas


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. FOLDER STRUCTURE & FILE CONVENTIONS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## /components
- One file per component (e.g., accordion.js, modal.js)
- Each file must be self-contained and not depend on other 
  component files (utils/ is okay to reference)
- Every component file must start with a metadata comment block:
  
    /**
     * Component: [Name]
     * Description: [What it does]
     * Dependencies: [jQuery / GSAP / none]
     * Webflow Load: [site-wide / page-specific]
     * CDN URL: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/.../components/[name].js
     */

## /interactions
- Animation and scroll-based effect scripts
- Always use GSAP for complex animations (loaded via CDN)
- ScrollTrigger plugin should be registered at top of file if used
- Do NOT hard-code pixel values — use relative/percentage values 
  or read from element dimensions dynamically

## /cms-scripts
- Node.js scripts only — these run locally, not in the browser
- Each script must be self-contained with clear CLI instructions
- Always use .env for API keys — never hardcode credentials
- Script files should be named by action: e.g., import-blog-posts.js,
  update-team-members.js, publish-site.js

## /utils
- Shared helper functions used across components
- Keep functions pure and well-commented
- Export as ES modules AND provide browser-compatible IIFE version
  where needed (Webflow's embed environment is not module-aware)


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. CLASS NAMING CONVENTIONS
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# [CUSTOMIZE] Update this as your Webflow project's class 
# naming patterns become established.

## General Rules
- Webflow classes use kebab-case: my-component-name
- Follow a loose BEM pattern: block__element--modifier
- Never modify Webflow-generated "combo classes" with JS 
  (classes that appear in italic in the Webflow designer)

## [CUSTOMIZE] Project-Specific Classes
- Utility prefix: u- (e.g., u-hidden, u-flex)
- Component prefix: c- (e.g., c-modal, c-accordion)
- JS hook prefix: js- (e.g., js-trigger, js-target)
  → js- classes are for JS targeting ONLY — no CSS attached to them
- State classes: is- (e.g., is-active, is-open, is-loading)


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. JAVASCRIPT STYLE GUIDE
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## General
- Use ES6+ syntax (arrow functions, const/let, template literals)
- Always use const unless reassignment is needed, then let
- Never use var
- Use descriptive variable names — no single-letter variables 
  except in short loops

## Comments
- Every function must have a JSDoc-style comment
- Explain WHY, not just WHAT, for non-obvious logic
- Mark todos as: // TODO: description
- Mark Webflow-specific workarounds as: // WEBFLOW: explanation

## Error Handling
- Always wrap API calls in try/catch
- Log errors with context: console.error('[ComponentName]:', error)
- Never silently swallow errors

## Module Pattern for Browser Files
- Since Webflow embeds don't support ES modules, use IIFE pattern 
  to avoid polluting global scope:

    (function($) {
      'use strict';
      
      // Your component code here
      
    })(jQuery);


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. WEBFLOW API (CMS SCRIPTS)
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## API Version
- Always use Webflow Data API v2
- Base URL: https://api.webflow.com/v2/
- Docs: https://developers.webflow.com/data/reference

## Authentication
- Bearer token authentication
- Token stored in .env as WEBFLOW_API_TOKEN
- Never log or expose the token

## [CUSTOMIZE] Your Site & Collection IDs
- Site ID: [YOUR_SITE_ID] 
  (Found in Webflow → Site Settings → General → Site ID)
- Collection IDs: [ADD AS YOU CREATE COLLECTIONS]
  (Found in Webflow → CMS → [Collection] → right-click → Copy Collection ID)

## Rate Limits
- Be aware of Webflow API rate limits (60 req/min on CMS plan)
- Add delay between bulk operations:
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));

## Always Confirm Before Destructive Operations
- Scripts that DELETE or bulk UPDATE must console.log a preview
  and require a manual confirmation (e.g., --confirm flag) before executing


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. LIBRARIES & DEPENDENCIES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## Always Available in Webflow (no import needed)
- jQuery 3.x → $, jQuery

## Load via CDN When Needed (add to Webflow head)
- GSAP: https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.5/gsap.min.js
- GSAP ScrollTrigger: https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.5/ScrollTrigger.min.js
- Swiper: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-bundle.min.js

## Node.js CMS Scripts (install locally)
- axios (HTTP requests to Webflow API)
- dotenv (environment variables)
- chalk (colored terminal output for readability)
- ora (loading spinners for long operations)


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. THINGS CURSOR SHOULD NEVER DO IN THIS PROJECT
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- Never use document.write()
- Never import/require jQuery (it's global)
- Never hardcode API keys, site IDs, or tokens in component files
- Never use ES module import/export syntax in /components or 
  /interactions files (Webflow embeds don't support modules)
- Never target Webflow combo classes with JavaScript
- Never use document.querySelector without checking the element 
  exists first (CMS pages render conditionally)
- Never assume a page has a specific element — always guard:
    const el = document.querySelector('.my-element');
    if (!el) return;


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 10. WORKFLOW REMINDERS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- After every commit to main, jsDelivr may cache for ~12 hours
  Use the purge URL to force immediate update during development
- Test all components in Webflow's Preview mode AND published mode
  (some behaviors differ between the two)
- Webflow's Designer canvas is NOT an accurate JS runtime — 
  always test real behavior in Preview or on the live/staging site
- Keep a comment at the top of each Webflow custom code block 
  indicating which CDN file it loads and what version/date

